name: MORNING, U IN MOURNING, U OUT
description: The cycles of our lives. We wake up in the morning and live our lives. You/"U" die and we place You/"U" in the word morning. This becomes mourning and we mourn that You/"U" are out and the cycle repeats the next morning until You, yourself are the one that dies and they are MOURNING, U OUT. It's a simple pattern of life and death that repeats over and over again, just reduced to its poetic abstract reality.
